originalText.text: Parked here on a Saturday and my car was damaged. The attendant told me to come back on Monday to file a claim with the manager. The claim was denied the same day because "I left the garage before filing the claim" and it's considered my fault.

originalText.text: The rudest person on planet earth. Don’t waste your money and time. Don’t park here. The owner should fire the staff.

originalText.text: The manager is good at his job, but the parking lot attendant has no sense of customer service at all and rude as hell.

originalText.text: Absolute joke. Had reservation with spot hero for Big East Tournament. Was supposed to be $26 for 930am until midnight. Returned at 5:30 and was told another $14 or I couldn't have the car back. Attendant told me spot hero is a separate fee. Called spot hero no answer.  Never use again and if spot hero does not reimburse I will never use them again.

originalText.text: Due to one narrow lane for entrance and exit, I was forced to wait on a gridlocked, one way 36th street blocking all traffic for blocks. There is no warning sign before you drive in. The attendant said matter of factly that this is a common occurrence and just said I had to back out while the car blocking me inside the garage took what seemed to be an eternity to load up his car. Would certainly not use this garage again.
